g.text: B-tree Page Format: Slotted Page (4096 bytes)

div.p: Collision Point When cell_content_start reaches header_size + 2 * cell_count, the page is FULL. Must split or redistribute
This design enables O(1) cell access via the pointer array while supporting variable-length cells without fragmentation between cells. Insert adds pointer at array end, cell at content end.

ul.li: first_freeblock (2): Offset to first free block (0=none)
cell_count (2): Number of cells on page
cell_content_start (2): First byte of cell content area
fragmented_bytes (1): Bytes in fragmented free space

div.p: Array of 2-byte big-endian offsets pointing to each cell's location. ptr[0] Cell 0 offset ptr[1] Cell 1 offset ptr[2] Cell 2 offset ... ptr[n-1] Cell n-1 offset Grows DOWNWARD toward free space.
Gap between cell pointers and cell content.
Actual cell data grows UPWARD from end. Table Leaf Cell: [payload_size:varint] [rowid:varint] [payload:bytes] [overflow_page:4bytes?] Table Internal Cell: [left_child:4bytes] [rowid:varint]
